<BODY>
<HEADLINE> United States Beat China in Juniors' Soccer Worlds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, June 27 (Xinhua) -- The American Florida surged
from one goal down to beat China 2-1 in the inaugural world
junior's soccer championships on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese squad, who were made up of players from Shenyang's
No. 131th middle school in North East China's Liaoning Province,
opened the scoring only two minutes after the kickoff.
</P>
<P>
But the Americans levelled the score eight minutes later on a
lapse of the Chinese defenders. The winner was net in the dying
minutes.
</P>
<P>
In the day's other matches, Brazil's Sao Paulo blanked
California of the United States 3-0 while Portugal beat Florida
3-1.
</P>
<P>
A total of 12 teams are taking part in the competition. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
