<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indonesia Backs Syrian Struggle to Regain Territory </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, June 27 (Xinhua) -- Indonesian President Soeharto
today reaffirmed Indonesia's full support for the struggle of the
Syrian people in regaining its territory from Israel.
</P>
<P>
"President Soeharto has reaffirmed Indonesia's support for the
Arab people, notably Syria, in regaining their territory from
Israel," Minister/State Secretary Moerdiono said here today
following talks between Soeharto and visiting Syrian Prime
Minister Mahmoud al-Zoubi at the Merdeka Palace.
</P>
<P>
During the talks, Soeharto stressed Indonesia's position not to
open diplomatic ties with Israel.
</P>
<P>
"So long as Israel does not fully comply with UN Security
Council resolutions 242, 338 and 425, Indonesia will not consider
the possibility of opening diplomatic relations with Israel,"
Soeharto was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
Besides discussing political affairs, the two leaders also
talked about ways to enhance the two countries' bilateral economic
and trade cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The Syrian prime minister arrived here Thursday for a five-day
state visit. 
</P>
</TEXT>
