<HEADLINE> African Opposition Parties to Form Forum </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, June 27 (Xinhua) -- Opposition parties from 13
African states have discussed setting up a forum to promote
democracy and dialogue in their countries.
</P>
<P>
The meeting was held in the Botswana's capital, Gaborone,the
Southern African Broadcasting Association reported.
</P>
<P>
A communique released today at the end of the two-day
gathering said the African opposition parties's forum also aims
to initiate, maintain and improve dialogue and communication
among the parties.
</P>
<P>
The meeting was attended by representatives of opposition
parties from 13 African Commonwealth countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
