<HEADLINE> European Commission Approves Humanitarian Aid for Albania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, June 27 (Xinhua) -- The European Commission said
today that it had approved a package of humanitarian aid worth
1.7 million ECU (some 1.9 million US dollars) for Albania.
</P>
<P>
The commission said the aid would be used to rehabilitate some
of the country's schools and health facilities that were looted and
damaged last March.
</P>
<P>
This package of aid will provide food for those dependents whom
they were unable to receive medical care because of the breakdown of
social welfare systems.
</P>
<P>
It will also provide badly-needed medicines and medical
supplies for many hospitals in Albania.
</P>
<P>
The aid, managed by the European Community Humanitarian Office,
will enable non-governmental organizations to carry out a
coordinated action over the next six months.  
</P>
</TEXT>
