<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kazakhstan Denies Sale of High-Tech Weapons </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALMA ATA, June 27 (Xinhua) -- Kazakhstan's Foreign Ministry
today denied western media reports that the country planned to
sell advanced air-defense systems and ground-to-air missiles to
Middle East and Asian countries.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman was quoted by the press here today as saying that
Kazakhstan has adhered strictly to international commitments on
non-proliferation of nuclear technology and high-tech weapons
systems.
</P>
<P>
The ministry statement said Kazakhstan firmly supports policies
promoting peace and stability throughout the world.
</P>
<P>
Kazakhstan has voluntarily given up its rights to inherit the
nuclear arsenal left on its soil by the former Soviet Union and
signed the Nuclear Non-Proliferation Treaty, the statement said.
</P>
<P>
Kazakhstan was, is and will be a force to safeguard world
peace, it said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
