<HEADLINE> Angola Invests 10 Million U.S. Dolalrs in Bread </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAUNDA, June 27 (Xinhua) --Angola plans to invest 10 million
U.S.Dollars in the bread making sector this year, said a document
issued today by the Research and Planning Department of the Angolan
Ministry of Industry.
</P>
<P>
Of the investments, 3 million U.S.Dollars will be used to
expand the production capacity of the country's bread bakeries
and the rest will go to the importation of the bread making raw
materials, the document said.
</P>
<P>
It said that since Angola began the immplementation of its
plan to increase nationwide bread supply in June 1996,
entreprenurs have provided an investment of 3 million U.S.
Dollars to the bread making sector so as to resume and expand the
bread production in the country.
</P>
<P>
Since June 1996, the Luanda flour mill and another two bread
bakeries with high prodcution capacity have been built up and
bread supply has been greatly improved, especially in Luanda,
Benguela, Bie and Huila provinces. 
</P>
</TEXT>
