<HEADLINE> Return of H.K. Good for World: Kenyan General </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, June 27 (Xinhua) -- The return of Hong Kong to China
is good, not only for China, but also for the whole world,
General Daudi Tonje, Kenya's Chief of General Staff of the Armed
Forces, said on his departure for Hong Kong today.
</P>
<P>
Tonje left here for Hong Kong to attend the grand ceremony of
the transfer of power of Hong Kong from the British Hong Kong
authorities to China scheduled for July 1. After the ceremony, he
will pay a 10-day visit to Beijing.
</P>
<P>
He expressed his belief that Hong Kong will maintain stability
and prosperity after its return to China.
</P>
<P>
"Not only Hong Kong, but also the whole of China will surely
have a better future," said Tonje, the highest-ranking Kenyan
military officer ever to visit China.
</P>
<P>
He described China's "one country, two systems" concept as
"splendid", noting "Definitely, it is working."
</P>
<P>
"There is a lot we can learn from China," he said, predicting
his visit will enhance the cooperation and friendly relations
already existing between the two countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
