<HEADLINE> Botswanan President to Visit Tanzania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, June 27 (Xinhua) -- President of Botswana, Sir
Ketumile Masire is expected to arrive in Dar es Salaam on Monday
for a four-day state visit at the invitation of Tanzanian
President Benjamin Mkapa.
</P>
<P>
According to a press release issued here today by the
Tanzanian Ministry of Foreign Affairs, during his visit in
Tanzania, the Botswanan president will hold talks with Tanzanian
leaders on development of relations between the two countries.
The talks will also cover regional, continental and international
issues.
</P>
<P>
Tanzania and Botswana are both members of the Southern African
Development Community (SADC) and share common views on a number
of African and international issues. 
</P>
