<HEADLINE> FN Euro-Deputy Sues Anti-FN Militant for Racial Injury </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 27 (Xinhua) -- The extreme-right National Front
(FN) party of Jean-Marie Le Pen is known for its open racial
discrimination against African, Arab and Asian immigrants, but
this time things seem to be all screwed up.
</P>
<P>
An FN European Parliament deputy from the French Antilles today
sued an anti-FN militant for racial injury.
</P>
<P>
Bernard Antony, the Euro-deputy from the party of Le Pen, sued
Denis Lebon for racial injury inflicted upon Stephane Durbec, a
regional councillor of FN in the southeastern
Provence-Alpes-Cote-d'Azur (PACA).
</P>
<P>
Wearing a tricolor waistband, Durbec joined an FN demonstration
held on January 26 in Vitrolles in PACA to support the municipal
campaign by FN candidate Catherine Megret, who became the mayor of
Vitrolles one week later.
</P>
<P>
Lebon reportedly shouted to Durbec: ``You don't have any shame!
You are a genetic error!"
</P>
<P>
Although he admitted having uttered these words, Lebon said
that he was saying that to a black friend of his, who he said
wanted to appear as an FN supporter in order to have a tricolor
sling for himself.
</P>
<P>
The FN militants usually wear tricolor waistband, which
represents the national flag of France, in public demonstrations.
</P>
</TEXT>
