<HEADLINE> Russian Defense Minister to Start Reform Goal for Army </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, June 27 (Xinhua) -- Russian Defense Minister Igor
Sergeyev on Friday outlined the tasks of the Russian army reform
in July at a meeting of the leadership of the Russian Armed
Forces.
</P>
<P>
According to the Ministry's press service, the meeting aimed at
summing up the reform tasks in June would be regular and should
not worsen the combat readiness and decline the effectiveness of
the reform in the Armed Forces.
</P>
<P>
At the meeting Sergeyev drew up the tasks of the army reform
in July, including the economic support for all proposals for the
accomplishment of the tasks.
</P>
<P>
Among other tasks is the strengthening of the law and order, as
well as discipline as the main criteria of the combat readiness,
the erasing of different errors and their reasons, and the
economical use of finances and other resources.
</P>
<P>
The Russian Defense Minister today also outlined the key points
of the armed reform in the newspaper "Krasnaya Zvezta" (Red Star).
</P>
<P>
These are, Sergeyev said, rationalizing the construction,
weapons and staff, improving the quality of military officials,
raising effect and quality of military education and training,
strengthening discipline and legal system, increasing the
technological equipment of the army and forming reasonable
foundation of military installations.
</P>
<P>
It is said that the Russian military construction will step by
step cut the armed services from the present five to three in the
end.  
</P>
</TEXT>
