<HEADLINE> Ethiopian FM on Return of Hong Kong to China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, June 27 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopian Foreign Minister
Seyoum Mesfin said this evening that the return of Hong Kong to
China is not only a big event to the Chinese people, but also the
world people.
</P>
<P>
He made the remarks at a reception given here by Chinese
Ambassador to Ethiopia Jiang Zhengyun on the occasion of the
resumption of the exercise of sovereignty over Hong Kong by the
People's Republic of China on July 1, 1997.
</P>
<P>
The minister said the Ethiopian government is very glad
to see the smooth return of Hong Kong to China.
</P>
<P>
He said that the ''one country, two systems'' principle is a
great concept. He believed that this concept will also be suitable
to the solution of the Taiwan problem.
</P>
<P>
The reception was attended by more than 400 guests
including Ethiopian Speaker of House of People's Representaitves
Dawit Yohannes, Deputy Speaker of House of People's Representatives
Petros Olango, Minister of Information and Culture Woldemichael
Chamo, Minister of Labour and Social Affairs Hassen Abdella,
and Minister of Trade and Industry Kassahun Ayele.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, a photo exhibition on Hong Kong was opened at the
reception.
</P>
<P>
The five-day exhibition will be continued to show at the Addis
Ababa City Hall and the Addis Ababa University respectively
