<HEADLINE> hkhk-Memories of Deng Xiaoping Cherished in Hong Kong Prior to Return (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Hong Kong, June 28 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong people cherish the
memories of Deng Xiaoping, the late Chinese leader who passed away
early this year, as the day when China resumes the exercises of
sovereignty over Hong Kong draws near.
</P>
<P>
"How I wish he could come to Hong Kong," said Ann Tse Kai, a
well-known Hong Kong figure.
"I had an opportunity to meet and talk with him," recalled Ann,
who is a vice-chairman of the National Committee of the Chinese
People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC). "I often tell
myself that it's lucky for China and the Chinese people to have
had such a great man as Deng."
</P>
<P>
He said that he felt some consolation in the release on July 1
of a picture album entitled "Deng Xiaoping and Hong Kong." Many
prominent Hong Kong figures including Ann himself, Fok Ying Tung
and Tung Chee Hwa are advisors for the album.
The picture album carries 100 precious photos that record Deng
Xiaoping's outstanding contributions to the settlement of the Hong
Kong question and his charisma in various historical events.
</P>
<P>
Deng Xiaoping remarked on many occasions: "I will pay a visit
to Hong Kong even if I have to go there in a wheelchair when China
resumes the exercise of sovereignty over Hong Kong."
</P>
<P>
Said Irene Wong, a business manager while hurrying to her Wan
Chai office: "I feel sad whenever it comes to my mind that Mr.
Deng Xiaoping cannot attend the grand ceremony marking Hong Kong's
return.
</P>
<P>
"But I'm glad that Deng's widow and his daughter will attend
the handover ceremony with the Chinese government delegation.
</P>
<P>
"Deng Xiaoping was a great man who has been respected by us
Hong Kong people."
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
