<HEADLINE> hkhk-Memories of Deng Xiaoping Cherished in Hong Kong Prior to Return (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Books on Deng Xiaoping and special sections in local book
stores selling color pictures of him attract many readers. "My
Father Deng Xiaoping," a biography by his daughter Deng Rong, was
once sold out in some local book stores.
</P>
<P>
"I've never had a chance to see him, but I have been told by my
teachers that Deng Xiaoping is a national hero and the pride of
the Chinese nation," said a student from Pui Kiu Middle School,
who was reading a book entitled "Deng Xiaoping on the Hong Kong
Question" in a book store attached to the Commercial Press (HK)
Ltd. in Causeway Bay.
</P>
<P>
At the subway station in Wan Chai is a giant color photo of
Deng Xiaoping. Many people stopped in front of it and looked at it
in silent respect. Deng souvenirs have been favorable items for
collection for many people.
</P>
<P>
"We Hong Kong people cherish the memories of Deng Xiaoping,"
said Ye, a cab driver, whose cab has a Deng picture hanging
behind the windshield.
</P>
<P>
Ng Hong Mun, honorary president of Hong Kong Federation of
Education Workers, recalled his two meetings with Deng Xiaoping:
the first was in June, 1982 when Deng emphasized that Hong Kong's
capitalist system will remain unchanged; the second time was in
May 1984 when Deng stressed that China will never be equivocal on
the matter of sovereignty.
</P>
<P>
"Deng Xiaoping spoke in a decisive manner, never beating about
the bush," Ng said.
</P>
<P>
Said Yau, a district board member: "Only with the policy of
'one country, two systems' put forward by Deng Xiaoping can the
Hong Kong question be solved.
</P>
<P>
"This is an unprecedented concept which demonstrates Deng
Xiaoping's great wisdom and courage."
</P>
<P>
W.H.Choi, president of Hong Kong Chinese Reform Association
said:  "Deng Xiaoping has drawn a beautiful blueprint for Hong
Kong. Under his 'one country, two systems' principle, we can build
a new Hong Kong that enjoys sustained prosperity. I'm sure we can
live up to Deng's expectations."  
</P>
