<HEADLINE> Beijing Ready for Activities Marking Hong Kong's Return </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 28 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese capital is ready for
the major activities marking Hong Kong's return to the motherland,
according to local sources.
</P>
<P>
Tian'anmen Square, which will hold a gala party on June 30,
have been thoroughly made over. Before the midnight handover
ceremony in Hong Kong, thousands of people will gather in the
world's largest square for the ceremony. Two gigantic platforms
for performances and two large TV screens to provide a live
broadcast of the ceremony have been set up, and the broadcast
equipment has finished its testing.
</P>
<P>
Six big neon lights, 160 red lanterns, and smaller lights on
pine trees in the square give it a new appearance.
</P>
<P>
A rally will be held in Workers' Stadium on July 1. Beijing
organizers have held dress rehearsals for it.
</P>
<P>
Beijing authorities have also decided to set off fireworks on
both June 30 and July 1. After two months of preparations, 1,100
armed policemen and 142 fireworks guns are ready for the show.
</P>
<P>
There are also 100,000 red banners, 600,000 flower pots, and
lights and lanterns along Beijing's main streets.
</P>
<P>
The enthusiasm of the city's citizens is strong in spite of the
hot weather of recent days. Some 200,000 people last night
gathered in Tian'anmen Square to look the scene over and to take
pictures. 
</P>
</TEXT>
