<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Sincerity in "One Country, Two Systems" Policy is Beyond   Any Doubt: Thai Consul General </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 28 (Xinhua) -- Thai Consul-General Rathakit
Manathat said here today he is convinced that Hong Kong will
continue to develop after it return to China and that he has full
confidence in its future.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with Xinhua, he said the policy of "one
country, two systems" China has set forth will benefit not only
Hong Kong's development also the development of China's interior
area.
</P>
<P>
"We have had contacts with China for many years, and know very
clearly that the Chinese government always means what it says. I
do not doubt China's sincerity in implementing this policy and I
am sure this policy will be implemented fully," he said.
</P>
<P>
On Hong Kong's prospects after the return, Hong Kong and the
interior area will become an integrated market, which is expected
to provide a good opportunity for Thailand, he said.
</P>
<P>
In the wake of the continued growth in friendly ties between
Thailand and Hong Kong, he said, the Thailand-Hong Kong Trade
Association that Thailand had set up here will give scope to its
active role in Thai-Hong Kong trade, while Thailand will join Hong
Kong to edge into the market in China's interior area and benefit
from it.
</P>
<P>
An estimated 25,000 Thai people now reside in Hong Kong. Many
came with their ancestors and have their homes here. "In general,
I can say they are very happy living in Hong Kong," he said.
</P>
<P>
To enhance people-to-people contact, the Thailand has decided
to establish a Thai Study Center early next month. The Roy
Highness Princess Maha Chakri Sirindhorn is expected to officiate
the study center when she comes to Hong Kong to attend the
handover ceremony, he said.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, Thailand will negotiate with the incoming government
of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR) on the
founding of a Thai-Hong Kong friendship association within the
year.
</P>
<P>
On bilateral economic and trade ties, the consul-general said
that there are nearly 200 Thai companies operating in Hong Kong
with a total investment of two billion HK dollars.
</P>
<P>
"We are a major exporter of rice, and 70 percent of the rice
consumed here are imported from Thailand," he said.
</P>
<P>
Thailand is the 11th trade partner of Hong Kong with a trade
volume of more than 60 billion HK dollars in recent years, he
said.
</P>
<P>
Furthermore, Hong Kong is also a leading investor in Thailand.
It has made a total investment of 15.5 billion HK dollars in the
fields of auto parts, computers, electronics, textiles and high
technology.
</P>
<P>
In future, he noted, Hong Kong investment will extend steadily
to Laos, Cambodia and Viet Nam.
</P>
<P>
As Thailand has always been an attractive tourist destination,
400,000 Hong Kong tourists visited Thailand last year and some
60,000 Thais came to visit Hong Kong, he said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
