<HEADLINE> Macao Radio to Broadcast HK's Handover Live </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, June 28 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese Channel of Radio Macao
is to broadcast the Hong Kong handover ceremony live from June
30 to July 1.
</P>
<P>
The radio station is sending a team of reporters to Hong Kong
to cover the historical event, including the handover ceremony and
 the activities marking the establishment of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (HKSAR), according to a report in today's
Macao Daily News.
</P>
<P>
The live broadcast will start at four o'clock on the afternoon
of June 30 and last until the morning of July 1. The radio
station also plans to extend its news program during the period.
</P>
<P>
Macao media has markedly increased reporting on Hong Kong
since early May. Leading Chinese language newspapers like the
Macao Daily, the Va Kio newspaper and the Tai Chung Pou newspaper
all have devoted whole pages to Hong Kong each day.  
