<HEADLINE> Romanian Police Crack Fake Dollar Crime Ring </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, June 28 (Xinhua) -- Romanian police have uncovered
an international crime ring trying to smuggle forged U.S. dollars
into the country, the media reported here today.
</P>
<P>
Police in the western city of Timisoara arrested a Romanian
man Gheorghe Raichici after a tip off.
</P>
<P>
He was trying to change 8,900 dollars worth of fake 100-dollar
bills in the market. Police said the forged money was
manufactured in Iran.
</P>
<P>
After questionning, Raichici confessed that he was a member of
an international criminal ring producing forged money and was
about to bring one million dollars worth of fake dollar bills into
Romania.
</P>
<P>
Several other people have been arrested in connection with the
case and police investigations are continuing. 
</P>
</TEXT>
