<HEADLINE> Senior Chinese Party Leader Meets Guinean Delegation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 28 (Xinhua)-- Hu Jintao, a member of the Standing
Committee of the Political Bureau of the Chinese Communist Party
Central Committee, met here today with Aboubacar Sompare, the
general secretary of the Party for Unity and Progress of Guinea.
</P>
<P>
Hu noted that Guinea was the first sub-Saharan country to
establish diplomatic ties with China, and that friendly and
cooperative relations between the two countries have developed
smoothly and healthily thanks to the joint efforts of years.
</P>
<P>
He said that China greatly appreciates Guinea's "one China"
position and thanks Guinea for its support in human rights and
other international affairs.
</P>
<P>
He said he was happy about the establishment of friendly links
between the CPC and the Party for Unity and Progress. These links
will further enhance mutual understanding and friendship between
the two peoples and will promote the advancement of bilateral
relations of mutual trust and all-round cooperation, he said.
</P>
<P>
Sompare conveyed the regards of Guinean President Lansana Conte
to President Jiang Zemin and other Chinese leaders. Guinea and
China and their people are mutually-trusted friends and their
friendship is established on the basis of friendly
cooperation. Guinea hopes to further strengthen the cooperation
between the parties and the governments of the two countries in
all fields, he said.
</P>
<P>
He also offered his congratulations to China on its resumption
of the exercise of sovereignty over Hong Kong. The Guinean people
are excited about this and they wish to share the excitement of
the Chinese people on the return of Hong Kong, he said.
</P>
<P>
Li Shuzheng, head of the International Department of the CPC
Central Committee, attended the meeting.
</P>
<P>
The Guinean delegation arrived here Friday and is scheduled to
visit Tianjin and Zhengzhou.  
</P>
