<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK-Macao Ferry Expects New Price Rise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, June 28 (Xinhua) -- The three ferryboat companies
running services between Hong Kong and Macao have applied to
increase ferry fares, and their applications are expected to be
approved by the Macao Government.
</P>
<P>
The average increase of the fare is about six percent, the same
level as last year's increase. After getting approval, the ferry
companies would adopt the new price from September.
</P>
<P>
The current price of a ferry trip between Macao and Hong Kong
has doubled that of 1990, following annual price rises.
</P>
<P>
Currently, a round ferry trip between Hong Kong and Macao on
economy class costs about 300 patacas (about 38 US dollars).
Passengers have to pay higher fees on holidays and at night.
</P>
<P>
Figures show that since 1994, the number of passengers taking
ferries between Hong Kong and Macao has dropped at a rate of about
three percent year by year, partly because they have had more
options to travel to the Pearl River Delta. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970628.0065 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-28 </DATE_TIME>
