<HEADLINE> China Beats Thailand in Women's Volleyball </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, June 28 (Xinhua) -- China defeated Thailand in
straight sets in a qualifying match for the World Women's
Volleyball Championships here on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese women spikers beat their Thai rivals 15-12, 15-12
and 15-5.
</P>
<P>
In another match of the day, Indonesia outplayed Australia
15-12, 15-6 and 15-5. 
</P>
