<HEADLINE> Schumacher Wins Pole Position for French Grand Prix </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 28 (Xinhua) -- German Formula One star Michael
Schumacher on Saturday won the pole position for the French Grand
Prix in the qualifying session in Magny-cours on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Schumacher, in his Ferrari, clocked the best time of one minute
14.548 seconds.
</P>
<P>
But the World championship leader Schumacher was challenged
strongly by both his 21-year-old brother Ralf, in a Jordan, and
fellow German Heinz-Harald Frentzen in a Williams.
</P>
<P>
Frentzen will share the front row of the grid with Schumacher,
whose pole was the 16th of his career and his second in succession
this year. Frentzen clocked 1:14.749.
</P>
<P>
Ralf Schumacher was third fastest, the younger of the two
racing drivers from Kerpen grabbing the best grid spot of his
fledgling Formula One career.
</P>
<P>
Canadian Jacques Villeneuve, who is second in the title
race, wound up fourth fastest in the second Williams. 
