<DOCNO> XIE19970628.0069 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> FM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, June 28 (Xinhua) -- Singapore is confident of the
future Hong Kong and the close synergy of Hong Kong and China's
inland areas will boost economic growth and development in the
Asia-Pacific, Foreign Minister S. Jayakumar said in a written
interview with Xinhua here today.
</P>
<P>
Singapore already has significant investments in both Hong Kong
and China's inland areas, he said, noting that as of the end of
1995, Singapore's private sector investments in Hong Kong amounted
to 4.47 billion US dollars and in China's inland areas, 2.1
billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
In addition, he said, there are investments from Singapore's
Government Investment Corporation and statutory boards. These
investments in real estate in Hong Kong and China's main cities
amounted to another two billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Singapore's economic ties with Hong Kong and China's inland
areas are "firmly anchored and will continue to flourish," he
said.
</P>
<P>
Jayakumar also said that Singapore already enjoys a
multi-faceted relationship with Hong Kong, which becomes a Special
Administrative Region of the People's Republic of China on July 1
this year.
</P>
<P>
With China, Singapore's close ties also go beyond the economic
sphere, he said.  "We have built up and will continue to develop
a broad-based relationship with China, which includes frequent
people-to-people, as well as government-to-government exchanges,
in the fields of culture, education, human resource management,
city-planning and various aspects of civil administration."
</P>
<P>
The Foreign Minister also expressed his confidence in that Hong
Kong will continue to prosper with the implementation of the
concept of "One country, two systems,", saying that the idea will
work because it is in the interest of both Hong Kong and China's
inland areas to make it work.
</P>
<P>
The "one country, two systems" formula "is an ingenious yet
practical and pragmatic formula for dealing with the issues left
over from history," he commented.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government has given the assurance that under this
formula, the principles of a "high degree of autonomy" for Hong
Kong and "Hong Kong people governing Hong Kong" will prevail. The
formula gives the Hong Kong people the right to continue to manage
their free-market system, including their own currency and an
independent monetary authority, he noted.
</P>
<P>
He said the return of Hong Kong to China "will therefore enable
Hong Kong to continue performing its role in much the same way as
it has been doing in the past".
</P>
<P>
On the economic development in Hong Kong and China's inland
areas, the minister said, Hong Kong played a major complementary
role for China's economy even before the handover.
</P>
<P>
After July 1, Hong Kong's complementary role in China's
economic growth will be even more pronounced, as countries in the
Asia-Pacific and around the world seek to capitalize on the
enormous opportunities offered by the rapidly developing Chinese
economy, he pointed out.
</P>
<P>
"The close synergy of both will boost economic growth and
development in the Asia-Pacific," he said.
</P>
<P>
The Singapore Foreign Ministry announced on Friday that
Minister Jayakumar has been invited to attend the official
Handover Ceremony in Hong Kong. He will be attending the Handover
Ceremony and other official events on June 30 and July 1 in Hong
Kong.  
</P>
</TEXT>
