<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kuwaiti Domestic Bank Assets Up Sharply in May </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, June 28 (Xinhua) -- The total assets of Kuwait's
domestic banks registered a highest monthly growth rate since 1991
of two percent in May, to reach 12 billion Dinar (about 39.6
billion U.S. dollars), a bank bulletin said today.
</P>
<P>
According to the document released by the Kuwaiti Central Bank,
the bank assets increased by 236.6 million Dinar (about 780
million U.S. dollars) in May, two percent higher than in April
when the assets stood at 11.8 billion Dinar (about 38.9 billion
dollars).
</P>
<P>
The assets include cash balances, net foreign assets, money
supply and private sector deposits, the bulletins said.
</P>
<P>
It added that the rise was due to a 296 million Dinar (about
976 million dollars) hike in domestic Dinar deposits though
foreign currency denominated deposits dropped by an equivalent of
117 million dinar (about 387 million dollars).
</P>
<P>
Money supply was up in May while total finances for Kuwaiti
imports dipped, the bulletin said.
</P>
<P>
It said the Kuwait Dinar remained stable against the dollar
with a fluctuation of a marginal 0.22 percent in favor of the
dollar. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
