<HEADLINE> China Orders First Cellular Terminal from Ericsson </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 28 (Xinhua) -- Jiangsu Province in east China has
signed a contract on a fixed cellular terminal (FCT) from
Ericsson, the first of its kind for China.
</P>
<P>
The unit helps replace wire transmissions with wireless
transmission.
</P>
<P>
Ericsson will provide 1,000 sets of its FCT-EF907 for improving
rural and urban communications in the province. The equipment will
be put in service by the end of September. By then, Jiangsu will
become the first province to use fixed cellular units as an
alternative to wire communications in China.
</P>
<P>
The FCT is useful in rural or remote regions or in older city
areas where lines are difficult to lay.
</P>
<P>
China is now the second largest market, after the US, for
Ericsson, which has 19 offices and nine joint ventures in China.
</P>
</TEXT>
