<HEADLINE> High-Tech Exhibition Opens in Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 28 (Xinhua) -- Holiday-makers in Hong Kong
flocked to an exhibition that opened here today to display the
latest high-tech development in Hong Kong and other parts of
China.
</P>
<P>
On show at the exhibition, "Technology for Tomorrow --
High-Tech Exhibition," are over 300 items of leader-edge
technology products, covering 15 technical areas including
aerospace, automation, biology, new materials, laser,
shipbuilding, environmental protection and information, some of
which represent the highest international standard, organizers
said.
</P>
<P>
"We have organized this large-scale high-tech exhibition not
only to celebrate Hong Kong's return to China, but also to promote
the interest of the general public in development and application
of high technology", said Edmund K H Leung, Chairman of the
organizing committee.
</P>
<P>
According to Leung, this exhibition shows the direction for
the development of tomorrow.
</P>
<P>
Jointly sponsored by the Hong Kong Science and Technology
sector for Celebration of Return of Sovereignty Association and
China Association for Science and Technology, the exhibition has
won widespread support from Hong Kong and the rest of China.
</P>
<P>
The City University of Hong Kong is providing a venue for the
exhibition free of charge while 22 ministries and bureaus of the
central government sent a large delegation to the exhibition.
</P>
<P>
Guo Huadong, research fellow with the Remote Sensing
Application Institute of the Chinese Academy of Sciences, said
that after July 1, cooperation between China's interior areas and
Hong Kong will spur the development of the country's high-tech
industries.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese Academy of Sciences and the Chinese University of
Hong Kong plan to jointly build a laboratory for the global
information science. 
</P>
</TEXT>
