<HEADLINE> Saudi Crown Prince Leaves Beirut </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, June 28 (Xinhua) -- Saudi Crown Prince Abdullah Ibn
Abdul-Aziz left here this afternoon after winding up a three-day
visit in Lebanon, the first by a senior Saudi royalty since 1975.
</P>
<P>
The Saudi crown prince, accompanied by a 140-member entourage,
was heading by road for Damascus.
</P>
<P>
The crown prince spent a relaxed time in Beirut, during
which his only official activities were to take joint dinners
with the Lebanese leaders, but many Lebanese officials believe
that an influx of Saudi investment to Lebanon will follow the
visit.
</P>
<P>
At a press conference, the Saudi foreign minister Saud
al-Faisal Al-Saud, underlined his country's blessing for the
establishment of an Arab common market proposed by Syria and Egypt.
</P>
<P>
Local daily Nida Al-Watan, which is famed for its access to
foreign ministry officials, reported today that the Saudi side
informed the Lebanese it would not attend a regional economic
conference to be held in Qatar in November.
</P>
<P>
Lebanon and Syria have announced that they will boycott the
regional economic summit, the fourth of its kind since four
years, due to an Israeli participation, and called for an Arab
economic summit to take its place. 
</P>
</TEXT>
