<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Adopt Laws on Highways And Animal Epidemic Prevention </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 28 (Xinhua) -- China's highest legislative body,
the Standing Committee of the National People's Congress, today
began to review drafts of highway and animal epidemic prevention
laws.
</P>
<P>
The two drafts were reviewed and revised by the NPC Standing
Committee during its February session and are expected to be
passed by the Standing Committee during this session.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Ruiying and Li Guiying, members of the Standing
Committee, said that highway construction has developed rapidly
since the reform and opening up began and that it has played an
important role in the economy. They said they believe that a law
on highways is necessary to standardize China's highway
construction.
</P>
<P>
Participants also suggested revisions for the draft of the law
on highways before it is submitted for approval.
</P>
<P>
The majority of participants said that the draft of the law on
animal epidemic prevention is a good law and it embodies the
principle of giving priority to prevention. "It is easy to put
into operation and the articles on animal diseases and disease
control are concrete," they said.
</P>
<P>
Li Guiying predicts that the law will contribute much to animal
husbandry in China, to the development of agriculture, to the
rural economy, and to improving people's standard of living.
</P>
</TEXT>
