<HEADLINE> Zambia Moves to Collect Labor Market Data </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, June 28 (Xinhua) -- Zambia has set up a unit to
collect and process labor market information, Labor and Social
Security Minister Peter Machungwa said here Friday.
</P>
<P>
Machungwa said that with the increasing of the users of the
labor market information, it has become necessary to set up a
workshop to make it available, Zambia Daily Mail reported today.
</P>
<P>
He said Zambia is the the co-ordinator of the Southern African
Development Community (SADC) employment and labor sector and has
a duty of enhancing the capacity to capture and process as much
labor market information as possible in the SADC region.
</P>
<P>
No program could succeed without the involvement of main users
and that is why they are involving employers and worker
organizations to enable it to gain quality and quantity, said the
minister.
</P>
<P>
The purpose of the workshop is to provide forum for various
labor market players and enable them exchange views on the
problems affecting the Zambian labor market. 
</P>
