<HEADLINE> Unidentified Disease Hit 40 Students in Central </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, June 28 (Xinhua) -- An epidemic still remains to be
diagnosed hit 40 students in central Uganda, local newspaper "The
New Vision'' reported today.
</P>
<P>
Robinson Nsumba Lyazi, the head of a medical experts group
detecting the affected, said ''the students did not seem to have
any serious disease''.
</P>
<P>
Kihumuro Apuuli, the Director of Health Service, yesterday
told yesterday Mityana Hospital in central Mubende district not
to release any affected student until experts made some finding.
</P>
<P>
The disease appeared a week ago. The main symptoms of the
victims are: violent arm shaking, convulsions in the chest which
force the patients to wail.
</P>
<P>
Some local medical experts attributed the cause of the disease
to emotional anxiety, but the real cause is yet to be examined.
</P>
