<HEADLINE> UAE GDP Increases in 1996 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, June 28 (Xinhua) -- The gross domestic product
(GDP) of the United Arab Emirates rose by 10.9 percent in 1996
to some 45 billion U.S. dollars, a local newspaper said today.
</P>
<P>
The Arabic daily AL Bayan said that an annual report released
by the UAE's central bank Thursday attributed this increase to the
surge of oil prices last year when it reached an average of 22
U.S. dollars per barrel.
</P>
<P>
The UAE ranks the fourth in its oil reserves in the world and
the bulk of its government revenues is earned from petroleum
exports. 
</P>
