<HEADLINE> UAE Population Rises to 2.44 Million in 1996 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, June 28 (Xinhua) -- The population of the United
Arab Emirates (UAE) increased to 2.44 million in 1996, making a
2.5 percent rise compared with that in 1995.
</P>
<P>
The Arabic daily al Bayan quoted a UAE central bank annual
report released Thursday as saying that the males constituted 67
percent of the total population while the females comprised 33
percent.
</P>
<P>
The majority of the UAE nationals are Muslims.
</P>
<P>
Of the UAE population, three quarters are of foreign
nationalities, coming mainly from Asian countries like India,
Pakistan, Bangladesh, Sri Lanka, Iran and the Philippines.
</P>
