<HEADLINE> Flood Claims Two Lives in Northwest Iran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, June 28 (Xinhua) -- Flood has claimed lives of two
villagers and killed 884 heads of cattle in Iran's northwestern
province of Ardebil.
</P>
<P>
Iran's official news agency IRNA reported that rain, hailstorm
and flood have inflicted 60 billion rials (20 million
U.S. dollars) damage in the area in the past 10 days.
</P>
<P>
Ardebil Governor General Mahmoud Ahmadi-Nejad was quoted as
saying that the flood has so far destroyed over 16,000 hectares of
agricultural lands and orchards in different cities of Khalkhal,
Meshkin-Shahr, Pars-Abad, Bileh-Savar Moghan and Garmi.
</P>
<P>
The flood also cut off roads linking the rural districts and
inflicted damage on roads, bridges, and irrigation network in
various urban and rural areas, the official noted.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, a provincial official in the city of Meshkin-Shahr
said that two people were seriously injured in the city when a
house collapsed by the flood.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, the relief teams are offering
emergency help to the affected residents. Relief goods such as
tents, foodstuff and other essential goods have been distributed
among the flood victims. 
</P>
</TEXT>
