<HEADLINE> Bank of China to Open Branch in HK New Airport </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 28 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong Airport Authority
has issued to the Hong Kong Branch of the Bank of China and the
Bank of East Asia licenses to operate in the new airport set to
open in early 1998.
</P>
<P>
The two banks will open branches in the departure hall and the
shopping center in the arrival hall, according to a spokesman for
the Airport Authority.
</P>
<P>
The Bank of China's branch will cover a floor space of 270
square meters in the departure hall in Chek Lap Kok, with an
operational period of 50 months. The Bank of East Asia's branch
will cover a floor space of 132 square meters with an operational
period of 48 months.
</P>
<P>
The Hongkong and Shanghai Banking Corporation Limited was also
granted the license to handle ATM business in the non-restricted
zone of the airport.
</P>
<P>
According to the spokesman, the banking licenses in the new
airport were originally intended to be granted to those providing
the highest bidding. But Bank of China offered the highest prices
for both licenses.
</P>
<P>
Not wishing to see service monopolized by one single bank, the
Airport Authority granted one of the two licenses to the Bank of
East Asia.  
</P>
</TEXT>
