<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai Exhibits Works of Western Modern Art </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 28 (Xinhua) -- Masterpieces of Vincent Van Gogh,
Pablo Picasso, Henri Matisse and 44 other western artists began to
be exhibited at the Shanghai Museum from today.
</P>
<P>
It is the first exhibition to show so many original works of
western modern art to Chinese viewers.
</P>
<P>
A total of 54 paintings and four sculptures, from the
collection of Solomon R. Guggenheim Museum, New York, will be on
show until mid-September.
</P>
<P>
They include post-impressionist Paul Cezanne's "Assiette De
Peches" (1879-1880), Vincent Van Gogh's "Paysage Enneige"
(February 1888), and Georges Seurat's "Paysannes au Travail"
(1882-1883).
</P>
<P>
"L'Italienne" (1916) of the renowned fauvist master, Henri
Matisse, and Pablo Picasso's "Paysage De Ceret" (summer of 1911)
are also among the exhibits, said to be worth well over 100
million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Guggenheim Museum is famous for its collection of modern art,
particularly works of impressionist and abstract art, which belong
to the period between the late 19th century and the mid-20th
century.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai is the last stop of the museum's Asian and Pacific
exhibition tour, following Seoul, Singapore and Dunedin in New
Zealand. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
