<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, June 28 (Xinhua) -- The Malaysian authorities
will issue new passports for the country's citizens, incorporating
the latest security features, by September next year, the
Malaysian national news agency Bernama reported today.
</P>
<P>
A study conducted on the issuance of the new passport, based on
the smartcard, is at its final stage, Bernama reported, quoting
Deputy Home Minister Tajol Rosli Ghazali.
