<HEADLINE> Moldovan Economy Faces Difficulties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, June 27 (Xinhua) -- Moldova is facing economic
difficulties with all economic indices on the decline, a
government press release said.
</P>
<P>
The gross domestic product (GDP) in the five-month period
declined by 10 percent from that of the same period last year with
the industrial output falling 15 percent and the agricultural
output down by 9 percent.
</P>
<P>
Industrial enterprises in the country are short of funds,
materials and energy and sales are sluggish.
</P>
<P>
But the production of building materials, leather products,
meat and canned fruits has increased during the first five months
of this year.
</P>
<P>
Moldova's trade reached 610 million U.S. dollars. It imported
380 million dollars of goods and exported 230 million dollars of
goods. 
</P>
</TEXT>
