<HEADLINE> Three Killed in Russia Train Blast </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, June 28 (Xinhua) -- Three people were killed and seven
wounded as a bomb exploded in a Moscow-St. Petersburg passenger
train on Friday night, the Itar-Tass news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
An unidentified mat set off bomb in a toilet of the train when
it was running on the Barovennoye-Torbino railroad section, the
Okulovka district of the Novgorod region, 90 kilometers away from
the Chudovo railroad station, the report said.
