<HEADLINE> Bangladeshi Celebrities Hail Hong Kong's Return </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, June 28 (Xinhua) -- The smooth return of Hong Kong to
China is a great diplomatic success of the Chinese government,
which has been handling the issue very well, said Anwarul Amin,
President of Bangladesh-China People's Friendship Association.
</P>
<P>
In a recent interview with Xinhua, Amin praised China for its
patience and foresight in settling the Hong Kong issue and said
the Chinese government set a good example for other regions to
solve disputes through dialogue and peaceful means.
</P>
<P>
Amin, who was a chief executive of an international bank in
Beijing for seven years in the 1980s, said that only after July 1,
Hong Kong people can become the masters of their own land.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Rezaul Karim, a former Bangladeshi Ambassador to
China, told Xinhua in a separate interview that the Hong Kong's
return is a natural and inevitable outcome of the historical
trend.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong has been an impartible part of China and "it took
more than 150 years for restoring the lost territory to its
rightful owner," said Karim.
</P>
<P>
"The most important aspect of the transfer is that, it is not
only the return of the territory but the citizens and people of
Hong Kong back to the own people, with whom they have had the
traditional bound of unity through common race, language and
culture," said Karim.
</P>
<P>
"The concept of 'one country, two systems' is a realistic
scientific theory under the present international situation," said
Engineer F.R. Siddiuqi, President of Bangladesh--China Cultural,
Economic &AMP; Mass Communication Center.
</P>
<P>
"With Hong Kong's return to the embrace of the motherland, they
will become the masters of Hong Kong. So they are more confident
that they can build Hong Kong into a better place," said Siddiuqi,
who has visited China seven times.  
</P>
</TEXT>
