<DOCNO> XIE19970628.0140 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sino-British Minute on Transfer of HK Archives Signed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
This signals the fulfilment of another major task related
directly to the transfer of power, through prolonged efforts made
by both the Chinese and British sides.
</P>
<P>
The Sino-British Agreed Minute on the Transfer of the Hong
Kong Archives defines the nature, extent and the method of
transferring Hong Kong's foreign affairs, defense and local
affairs archives.
</P>
<P>
"The signing of the minute is, beyond any doubt, a direct
contribution to the transfer of power of Hong Kong," said Zhao
Jihua, senior Chinese representative of the Chinese side of the
JLG.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government has attached great importance to the
transfer of Hong Kong archives, since it constitutes an important
component part of the transfer of power of Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Consultations between the two sides started back in 1986, and
in 1990, both sides concluded the Agreed Record of Discussions in
the Sino-British Joint Liaison Group on the Question of Transfer
of Hong Kong Archives, which defined a number of major principles
concerning the transfer.
</P>
<P>
In order to implement the Agreed Minute, he noted, the two
sides continued consultations in the following year on specific
matters with regard to the transfer of the archives.
</P>
<P>
According to Zhao Jihua, in order to embody China's exercise
of sovereignty over Hong Kong, guarantee the effective
implementation of obligations of the Central government on matters
concerning foreign affairs and national defense, and ensure the
efficient administration of the Hong Kong Special Administrative
Region, all archives in Hong Kong, should, in principle, be
transferred to the Chinese central government in 1997.
</P>
<P>
To date, through flexible and pragmatic work, the transfer of
the archives on foreign affairs, defense and local affairs has all
been settled as signified in the minute signed today, Zhao said.
 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
