<HEADLINE> Northeast China Province Launches Anti-drug Campaign </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, June 28 (Xinhua) -- Northeast China's Liaoning
Province strengthened its crackdown on drug-related crimes in the
past two months, culminating on International Anti-Drug Day.
</P>
<P>
Shenyang, the provincial capital, has carred out a large-scale
campaign and called on all walks of life to combat narcotics.
</P>
<P>
Local police authorities in Anshan, an industrial city,
recently executed a convict charged for trafficking 360 grams of
heroin, the biggest case in the province. Another 14 criminals
were arrested for trafficking, holding or selling drugs.
</P>
<P>
Local sources revealed that the provincial authorities in the
past two years spiked 8,600 drug-related cases, confiscated 10 kg
of heroin and 29 kg of opium, and arrested 780 criminals, of whom
500 were sentenced to different terms in jail.  
</P>
