<HEADLINE> Police vow to Maintain Hong Kong's Security </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
According to Hui, who has been serving the police for 30 years,
Hong Kong recorded the lowest crime rate in 15 years in 1996, with
1,250 crime cases for per 100,000 people, thus becoming one of the
most secure cities in the world.
</P>
