<HEADLINE> PLA Troops Ready To Enter Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 28 (Xinhua) -- Trucks, naval vessels and aircraft
are all ready to take the People's Liberation Army (PLA) troops
now standing by to take over the defense of Hong Kong on July 1.
</P>
<P>
The PLA troops to be stationed in the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (SAR) have completed all training courses
according to plan. All preparations have been carefully done, and
the modernized logistic unit has already moved fuels, provisions
and medicine in place.
</P>
<P>
Resplendent in specially designed uniform and in high spirits,
the PLA men are awaiting orders to march.
</P>
<P>
"We are determined, confident and able to perform
satisfactorily in defense of the Hong Kong SAR, to win the trust
of the compatriots there and to accomplish the commission that the
motherland and the people have bestowed on us," an officer told
Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with Xinhua, General Liu Zhenwu, commander of
the Hong Kong SAR garrison, said that the troops have completed
all preparations for entering Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
He said that as an important symbol of China's sovereignty, the
PLA troops will perform their duties strictly in line with the
Basic Law and the Law Concerning Stationing Troops in the Hong
Kong SAR.
</P>
<P>
Called upon to safeguard the prosperity and stability of Hong
Kong, the troops will live up to the trust of the Central
Committee of the Communist Party of China (CPC) and the Central
Military Commission (CMC) and the people's expectations, he said.
</P>
<P>
The garrison troops were formed on January 28, 1996. All the
PLA troopers received intensified education on politics, law and
ethics. Every member of the troops knows all about the laws
concerning the Hong Kong SAR. Many of them have learned to speak
English and Cantonese. All the drivers have learned the local
traffic rules.
</P>
<P>
The expenses of the PLA troops stationed in Hong Kong will be
borned by the People's Central Government. The majority of the
provisions for the troops will come from the inland areas. 
</P>
</TEXT>
