<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Strictly Observe the Hong Kong Basic Law (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
It is China's basic state policy to introduce the "one country,
two systems" concept with regard to Hong Kong. The HKSAR Basic Law
embodies the principle of "one country, two systems" and all the
policies of the central government relating to Hong Kong. It is in
fact a legal vehicle for implementing the principle of "one
country, two systems".
</P>
<P>
The Basic Law was passed and promulgated by the supreme
legislative body -- the National People's Congress. It is a state
law with a universal binding force. It is also an important
component part of the legal system of China and the legal basis
for the operation of the HKSAR.
</P>
<P>
Implementation of the Basic Law strictly and in an all-round
manner means to uphold "one country" and "two systems", ensure a
high-degree of autonomy of the HKSAR, and guarantee that the
principle will remain "unchanged for fifty years".
</P>
<P>
By upholding "one country", it means to safeguard a unified
People's Republic of China, the unification and sovereignty of the
state and territorial integrity. This is the precondition for
establishing the HKSAR and for formulating the Basic Law.
</P>
<P>
It is in pursuance to the provisions of Article 31 of the
Constitution of the People's Republic of China that the Central
People's Government established the HKSAR and the National
People's Congress formulated and promulgated the HK Basic Law.
</P>
<P>
The government and people of the HKSAR, like the rest of the
country, are obliged to safeguard the unification, sovereignty and
territorial integrity of the country. They are obliged to
safeguard security of the country.
</P>
<P>
By upholding "two systems", it means to safeguard the socialist
system that is unswervingly pursued by the main body of the
country with a 1.2 billion people and at the same time
unswervingly safeguard the provisions of the Basic Law that "the
socialist system and policies shall not be practised in the Hong
Kong Special Administrative Region, and the previous capitalist
system ans way of life of Hong Kong shall remain unchanged."
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970628.0151 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Strictly Observe the Hong Kong Basic Law (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 28 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese people will greet the
birth the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region(HKSAR) on July 1
and the implementation of the Basic Law of the HKSAR on the same
date.
</P>
<P>
This will mark a new period of the implementation the "one
country, two systems" policy and usher in a new era in which "Hong
Kong will be governed by Hong Kong people" with a high-degree of
autonomy.
</P>
<P>
President Jiang Zemin emphasized not long ago that "to ensure
Hong Kong's smooth transfer and maintain its long-term stability
and prosperity after its return to the motherland concerns the
immediate interests of Hong Kong compatriots and the fundamental
interests of the Chinese nation as well as peace and development
in Asia and the world as a whole. We must do it well."
</P>
<P>
Jiang proposed the following in order to ensure that the job is
well done: unswervingly implement the grand concept of "one
country, two systems" advanced by Deng Xiaoping, unswervingly
implement the principle of "Hong Kong being governed by Hong
Kong people" with a high-degree of autonomy, and unswervingly
observe the Basic Law of the HKSAR.
</P>
<P>
"As HKSAR basic law is a national law,", he said, "Not only
should the people of Hong Kong but also all provinces, autonomous
regions, and municipalities must strictly abide by it."
</P>
</TEXT>
