<HEADLINE> Australia Beats New Zealand in World Cup Tie </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, June 28 (Xinhua) -- Australia sent a squad of
European-based players to Saturday's opening match of the World
Cup soccer Oceania Group finals in Auckland and they trounced New
Zealand 3-0.
</P>
<P>
With the victory, former English national head coach Terry
Venables has stretched his winning run with the Australians to 10
matches.
</P>
<P>
Australia's opening goal came after a defensive error, with
Italian-based Craig Foster connecting a loose ball to set up John
Aloisi midway through the first half.
</P>
<P>
The visitors went ahead 2-0 just before halftime as Spain-based
Aurelio Vidmar found the net in the 42nd minute. Craig Foster
completed the tally in the 67th minute.
</P>
<P>
New Zealand played the last 23 minutes with 10 men after
midfielder Chris Jackson was sent off for his second bookable
offense.
</P>
<P>
The return leg is in Sydney next Saturday and the winner will
take on the fourth-placed Asian team for a spot in the French
finals next year. 
</P>
