<HEADLINE> China Refutes Lies about Maltreatment of Wei Jingsheng </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 28 (Xinhua) -- A Chinese official has refuted
recent reports by overseas media that "Wei Jingsheng was
beaten up in prison" as "lies spread by certain individuals."
</P>
<P>
In an interview with Xinhua here today, a leading official from
the department of prison under the Ministry of Justice said that
the above-mentioned reports of Western media "do not tally with
the facts at all."
</P>
<P>
"At 9 a.m. on May 29 this year, when Wei Jingsheng was breaking
into the prison's warehouse without permission, an inmate who was
responsible for taking care of the warehouse tried to stop him,"
the prison official recounted.
</P>
<P>
"Wei flew into a rage, damaged the door by kicking it and beat
up the inmate," the official said, "But the inmate did not strike
back.
</P>
<P>
"The policeman on duty immediately stopped Wei's behavior and
criticized him for his serious mistake of violating the prison
rules," he said.
</P>
<P>
"Later Wei not only admitted his mistake but also said that he
would not make such a mistake again in the future," the official
said.
</P>
<P>
"Considering Wei Jingsheng's improved attitude toward his
mistake, the prison authorities decided not to give him any
penalty," he said.
</P>
<P>
"China's judicial departments protect the legal rights of
prisoners according to China's law," he said.
</P>
<P>
"Wei's health in prison is in normal condition and the reports
that 'Wei was beaten up in prison' and 'Wei did not receive
medical care for his illness' are sheer fabrications by certain
individuals," he said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
