<HEADLINE> Shanghai Better Prepared for Flood Season </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 28 (Xinhua) -- China's largest trade and
financial city will be safer than in previous years during the
impending flood risk season as a result of recent attention paid
to better local control facilities.
</P>
<P>
The city also plans to further invest massively over the next
four years to strengthen its flood water defenses, such as
embarkments, and to increase the number of sluice gates and pumps
along water courses.
</P>
<P>
Local officials say that the first phase of city projects
aiming to improve flood control works have been finished, with a
total of 55 km of embarkments being built or rebuilt, and 65
sluice gates and 29 pump stations added.
</P>
<P>
The second phase of the flood defense project work, costing 88
million yuan, is already underway. It involves the building or
rebuilding of 52 sluices and attention to 84 kilometers of
embarkments.
</P>
<P>
Officials say that flood control works in the western part of
the city were always vulnerable, and work to improve defenses on
that flank have been given priority. 
</P>
</TEXT>
