<HEADLINE> Chilean FM: Hong Kong's Return An Historical Event </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, June 27 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong's return to China is "a
most significant historical event," Chilean Foreign Minister Jose
Miguel Insulza told Xinhua in a written interview today.
</P>
<P>
Insulza hoped to further Chile's relations with Hong Kong and
China as a whole after the territory's return to the motherland on
July 1.
</P>
<P>
"No doubt a big event in China's diplomatic endeavors," he
said, the country's resumption of the exercise of sovereignty over
Hong Kong through peaceful means is also "a significant
undertaking for the international community."
</P>
<P>
"Equally encouraging is the fact that Hong Kong's return is
proceeded with economic and social stability, which is beneficial
to China's economic growth, private businesses holding interests
in Hong Kong and local residents there," he said.
</P>
<P>
Chile's membership at the Asia-Pacific Economic Cooperation
forum and exchanges with the South American Common Market and
other groups are a show of its willingness to "take an active part
in international economic integration," the minister noted.
</P>
<P>
His country's approach is providing the best opportunity for
exporters and investors in Hong Kong to use Chile as a staging
point for exploring the huge dynamic market of the entire Latin
America, he said.
</P>
<P>
He believed that "Hong Kong's return to China will help Chile
strengthen its economic relations with China, which poses as the
biggest single market in the world." 
</P>
