<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Road Accidents Claim 15 Lives in Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, June 28 (Xinhua) -- Road accidents left 15 dead and 108
others injured on Friday in different accidents in Bangladesh, the
local press reported here today.
</P>
<P>
On that day, nine people were killed and about 100 others
injured when a truck upturned on a highway in Gouripur County,
northern Mymensingh District.
</P>
<P>
Police and witnesses said the truck was carrying 150 people
from Iswarganj to the district town. Most of the passengers were
candidates for a written test for recruiting government primary
school teachers.
</P>
<P>
In southwestern Jessore District, five people were killed on
the spot and eight others injured when a passenger bus collided
head on with a private car in Ramnagar County.
</P>
<P>
Police said the mishap occurred on Friday morning when the
private car of a bridal party collided with the Khulna-bound bus.
</P>
<P>
In another accident which occurred in the capital Dhaka, a
student was killed and 10 others injured Friday afternoon near
Dhaka Medical College Hospital. All the victims were rushed to
hospital.  
</P>
</TEXT>
