<HEADLINE> WB Approves Credits for Projects in Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 27 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank today announced
the approval of three credits totaling 123.7 million U.S. dollars
for projects in Africa.
</P>
<P>
A credit of some 35 million dollars is provided for
Madagascar's urban infrastructure project to upgrade roads,
drainage and other infrastructure in Antananarivo and six towns.
</P>
<P>
Another credit of some 38.7 million dollars will be used to
assist Mali-Mauritania-Senegal regional hydropower development
project to build a power station with a 200 megawatt capacity at
the Manantali dam on the Bafing river in Mali, and transmission
lines to Mali, Mauritania and Senegal.
</P>
<P>
The World Bank also earmarked a 50 million dollar credit for
Rwanda to help it provide basic services to returning refugees and
assist economic recovery.
</P>
<P>
The credits will be channeled through the International
Development Association (IDA), the concessionary lending arm of
the World Bank for developing countries. 
</P>
