<HEADLINE> Mexico Welcomes Hong Kong's Return to China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Mexico respects China's theory
of "one country, two systems," and wishes its implementation to be
successful and to permit a smooth return of Hong Kong to China,
said a senior Foreign Ministry official here today.
</P>
<P>
The idea has a great historical meaning, as it will be a sample
worldwide for the way in which two economic systems can co-exist
in one country, said Eduardo Martinez, general director for the
Pacific and Asian Affairs at the Foreign Relations Ministry.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong's return on July 1 is a triumph of peace through a
peaceful solution, after an admirable process of negotiations
between Britain and China, Martines told Xinhua in an interview.
</P>
<P>
Martinez, who worked from 1978 to 1981 at the Mexican Embassy
in China, said the good performance of the "one country, two
systems" formula will help bring a bigger inflow of investments
and more dynamic commercial activities in China.
</P>
<P>
There also will be an atmosphere of confidence for the
political, economic, and cultural future of Hong Kong and China as
a whole, said Martinez.
</P>
<P>
Referring to Mexico's economic ties with Hong Kong, the
diplomat said exchanges will grow at a faster pace. Annual trade
between Mexico and the region is worth 500 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The Mexican government will send Foreign Minister Jose Angel
Gurria to be represented at the ceremony for Hong Kong's return.
</P>
</TEXT>
