<HEADLINE> Kazakhstan Paper: Hong Kong to Have New Growth Opportunities </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALMA ATA, June 27 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong's return to China will
breed new opportunities for the region's growth, said a full-page
article published today in the Kazakhstan Pravda.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong, now one of the most developed regions in the world,
will embrace a better future after China resumes the exercise of
sovereignty over the territory on July 1, said the article.
</P>
<P>
As a world trade and financial center, Hong Kong will help push
foward the Chinese mainland's development after the return, and
the role in turn will further its own prosperity, it asserted.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government's policy of "one country, two systems"
will keep Hong Kong's current social system intact and assure a
high-level of autonomy in the region's administration, it noted.
</P>
<P>
The policy, added the newspaper article, provides a guarantee
not only for Hong Kong's smooth return as a Special Administrative
Region, but also for its future prosperity and stability. 
