<HEADLINE> Shanghai to Hosts American Ginseng Trade Fair </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGCHUN, June 28 (Xinhua) -- A ginseng trade fair will be
held in Shanghai from August 8-11.
</P>
<P>
More than 70 domestic operations which cultivate, process and
market American ginseng will display products, hold trade talks
and symposiums on methods to develop their industry at the fair.
</P>
<P>
Foreign counterparts may be invited to take part, said the
event's organizer, the State Administration of Traditional Chinese
Medicine.
</P>
<P>
Though China is the world's third largest producer of the root,
after the United States and Canada, the scheduled event next month
will be the first ginseng promotional event ever to be held in the
country. Ginseng is highly valued for its health-inducing
properties.
</P>
<P>
American ginseng is cultivated in about 20 of China's
provinces, and they produce 100-150 tons of dried ginseng
annually, according to Lian Haozhe, head of a research institute
concerned with native products under the Chinese Academy of
Agricultural Sciences.
</P>
<P>
Quality of Chinese-cultivated American ginseng is rated equal
to that from the U.S. and Canada, claimed Lian, whose academy is
based in Changchun, capital of northeast China's Jilin Province.
</P>
<P>
Jilin is China's leading American ginseng producer. Its annual
output accounts for 60 percent of the national total.  
</P>
</TEXT>
