<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hong Kong is Leading Investor in Sichuan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, June 28 (Xinhua) -- As central government continues to
favor hinterland regions with more preferential policies to spur
economic development, Sichuan province is becoming an increasingly
attractive investment destination for Hong Kong businesses.
</P>
<P>
Sichuan has approved 2,375 Hong Kong-funded joint ventures
over the past few years, and latest statistics show that total
accumulated Hong Kong investment there hit 1.4 billion US
dollars. The figure is said to constitute 60 percent of all
overseas capital ever having entered the province.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong investment has tended to be directed towards civil
construction, energy, transportation, food processing, chemicals
and entertainment.
</P>
<P>
An official with the province's foreign trade department said
that Sichuan's export to Hong Kong last year reached 520 million
US dollars, accounting for 24 percent of the total while import
from Hong Kong registered 250 million US dollars, 14 percent of
the total.
</P>
<P>
Sichuan, though abundant in natural and labor resources, is now
in great need of investment capital. Local officials said the
province should seek a reciprocal trade agreement with Hong Kong
so as to create a more sound economic mix here after the
handover. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
