<HEADLINE> Sheringham Joins Manchester United </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 27 (Xinhua) -- English champions Manchester United
pulled off a huge surprise to the Premier soccer on Friday by
signing England striker Teddy Sheringham from Tottenham Hotspur.
</P>
<P>
Sheringham joined the European Cup semifinalists for a fee in
the region of 3.5 million pounds sterling ($5.8 million), which is
United's biggest close-season signing.
</P>
<P>
The transfer of the 31-year-old forward, who has enjoyed a
successful partnership with Alan Shearer in the national team, is
believed to have given a huge boost to United for next season.
</P>
<P>
United now have a quality attacking player to replace Frenchman
Eric Cantona who recently announced his retirement from the game.
</P>
<P>
Sheringham had been at Tottenham since 1992. Ironically his
first match for United could be against the London club at White
Hart Lane on August 10 on the opening weekend of the Premier
league season. 
</P>
</TEXT>
