<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Croatia Sails Further Despite Defeat </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, June 27 (Xinhua) -- Croatia secured its outing to the
second phase despite a 88-95 loss to Ukraine on Friday at the
European basketball championship.
</P>
<P>
Croatia, one of the favorites to win the competition, avoided
an early exit only after Spain beat Germany 67-59 in the same
group.
</P>
<P>
Ukraine was nevertheless eliminated, alongside Bosnia, Latvia
and Slovenia, all of whom finished bottom of their groups.
</P>
<P>
Spain won group D with three victories, while Germany, Ukraine
and Croatia finished level on points with one victory each, and
results of games between the teams were used to determine the
final standings.
</P>
<P>
With first-phase results also counting for the second phase,
the Croats will have to pull out all the stops to make it to the
quarter-finals.
</P>
<P>
While the Croats have been disappointing, Spain and Greece have
both exceeded expectations.
</P>
<P>
The hosts were held by a tough German defence but eventually
found their touch from the three-point line to pull away.
</P>
<P>
Pre-tournament favourites Yugoslavia won a convincing 108-89
victory over Latvia.
</P>
<P>
Greece had surprised all by winning all their three opening
games in group A, including a cliff-hanger against Bosnia.
</P>
<P>
With just three tenths of a second on the clock, Greece's
Fragiskos Alvertis fired in a three-pointer to clinch the 78-76
victory. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
