<HEADLINE> Former World Champion Fails in Comeback bid </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, June 27 (Xinhua) -- Former world champion Billy
Konchellah crashed out of the Kenyan world athletics championship
trials by finishing eighth in the 800 meters semi-finals here on
Friday.
</P>
<P>
The 35-year-old Kenyan returned to the track after being
sidelined by knee injuries for a year.
</P>
<P>
Konchellah's younger brother Patrick won his semi-final heat,
clocking one minute 45.59 seconds ahead of Olympic bronze
medallist Fred Onyancha (1:45.67) and David Kiptoo (1:45.84).
</P>
<P>
In the 10,000 meters final Paul Koech beat three-times world
cross-country champion Paul Tergat into third place. 
</P>
