<HEADLINE> Doohan Drives Fastest for Dutch Grand Prix </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMSTERDAM, June 27 (Xinhua) -- World champion Michael Doohan of
Australia drove his Honda on Friday to the fastest to qualify for
the Dutch 500cc Grand Prix in Assen.
</P>
<P>
Doohan clocked two minutes 2.512 seconds on the 6.05-km track,
on the brink of the record of 2:02.433 set by American Kevin
Schwantz in 1991.
</P>
<P>
Italian Aprilia rider Doriano Romboni was second fastest in
2:02.884.
</P>
<P>
"Things worked out okay in the end, although we did get caught
out by the rain a bit because I had to start the session
running-in a new engine," said Doohan, who has won the past three
races in Assen.
</P>
<P>
Doohan leads the championship with 145 points, 53 points clear
of his Spanish teammate Alex Criville who suffered severe injuries
to his wrist and hand in a crash on Thursday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
