<HEADLINE> Greece Urges Smooth Holding of Elections in Albania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, June 27 (Xinhua) -- Greece today called for a smooth
holding of general elections in neighboring Albania.
</P>
<P>
A statement released by the Greek Foreign Ministry late this
evening said that Athens believed that the smooth holding of
elections in Albania Sunday was "a fundamental prerequisite" in
promoting the democratic process, the achievement of political and
social stability, respect for human rights and economic
development.
</P>
<P>
"The Greek government hopes that the elections will lead to the
formation of a widely accepted government that will undertake
effectively the project of restoring the country," the statement
said.
</P>
<P>
The statement said that Greece had taken specific and
fundamental measures to help Albania nationals in Greece,
including members of the ethnic Greek minority, travel to Albania
to vote.
</P>
<P>
Greece was prepared to continue its contribution in the future
to efforts by the Albanian people to establish a modern,
democratic society, it said.
</P>
<P>
In a related development, a seven-member interparty
parliamentary delegation left here for Tirana today to act as
observers in the forthcoming elections. 
</P>
</TEXT>
