<HEADLINE> Bosnia to Export Electricity to Croatia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SARAJEVO, June 27 (Xinhua) -- The Bosnian power company
Elektroprivreda will export 320 million kilowatt hours of
electricity to Croatia by the end of this year, according to a
deal signed today.
</P>
<P>
The deal was signed by Emir Aganovic of Elektroprivreda and
Damir Begovic of the Croatian Electricity Board.
</P>
<P>
Aganovic said that the export amounts to 10 percent of the
electricity produced in Bosnia.
</P>
<P>
Sixty percent of the exported electricity will be paid in cash
and 40 percent in goods, local TV quoted Aganovic as saying.
</P>
