<HEADLINE> IFC Signs 250 Mln Dlr Financing Accords With Czech Company </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 27 (Xinhua) -- The International Finance
Corporation (IFC) today signed loan agreements totaling some 250
million U.S. dollars for Nova Hut, a.s., one of the Czech
Republic's principal steel producers.
</P>
<P>
The IFC financing, the largest ever arranged by the IFC in the
country, will help Nova Hut to embark on a comprehensive
modernization and environmental upgrade of its steel complex in
Ostrava, in the Moravia region of the country.
</P>
<P>
Nova Hut, which is in the process of being privatized, is one
of the first major Czech privatizations incorporating a
comprehensive investment program without a foreign strategic
investor. At present, it is an integrated steel company with an
annual production capacity of about 4 million tons of crude steel.
</P>
<P>
The project is expected to be completed by 2000 at a total cost
of some 650 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
The IFC's financing package consists of a 75 million dollar
loan for the IFC's own account and a 175 million dollar syndicated
loan for a total of 17 international financial institutions from
Japan, Germany, Austria, South Korea, the U.S., France and
Belgium.
</P>
<P>
The IFC is a member of the World Bank Group and the largest
multilateral source of equity and loan financing for private
projects in developing countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
