<HEADLINE> Crotian Court Certifies Tudjman's Reelection </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZAGREB, June 27 (Xinhua) - The Croatian Constitutional Court
today certified the reelection of President Franjo Tudjman,
according to local press reports.
</P>
<P>
The final results of the June 15 presidential elections were
61.41 percent for Tudjman of the Croatian Democratic Union, 21.03
percent for Social Democrat candidate Zdravko Tomac and 17.56
percent for nine-party candidate Vladimir Gotovac.
</P>
<P>
Under Croatia's election law, the results should be certified
by the constitutional court before Tudjman takes the office for
the third time in a row since the country's independence. 
</P>
